io.branch.referral

Class BranchLinkData

  • java.lang.Object
    • JSONObject
      • io.branch.referral.BranchLinkData

  • public class BranchLinkData
extends JSONObject

    The BranchLinkData object is based on JSONObject and expands the class to enable collections of tags.

    Tags are returned from the server, and form the data dictionary that each deep link shared via the Branch platform contains.

      • putTags

        public void putTags(java.util.Collection<java.lang.String> tags)
             throws JSONException
        Use this method to add tags to the data dictionary that will go along with the deep link that is being created.
        Parameters:
        tags - A Collection of String objects, each element of which contains a tag and value to be added to the data dictionary of a link.
        Throws:
        JSONException - Each item in the Collection needs to be of valid JSON format. If it is not, a JSONException will be thrown.
        See Also:
        #tags} - the variable set by this method.

      • hashCode

        public int hashCode()

        Calculates the hash for this object as currently configured and returns the resultant Integer.

        The hash value is a combination of the hashCode of:

        • alias
        • channel
        • feature
        • stage
        • params

        Changing any of these attributes will change the hashCode, making comparison straightforward.
